<header class="site-header">
  <span class="header-icon">🏠</span>
  <h1>StageCraft — AI Interior Design</h1>
  <div class="doc-type">Privacy Policy</div>
</header>
  <div class="container">
    <p class="meta">Package: <code>com.jaystudio.ai.home.interior.design</code><br />
    Last updated: May 16, 2026</p>

    <p>This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>Jay Studio</strong> (“we”, “us”, “our”) collects, uses, and shares information when you use the <strong>StageCraft — AI Interior Design</strong> mobile application (the “App”). By using the App, you agree to this policy.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <h3>1.1 Information you provide</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Room photos</strong> — images you upload or capture to generate AI interior designs.</li>
      <li><strong>Design preferences</strong> — room type, style, color palette, design mode, and optional custom text prompts.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>1.2 Information collected automatically</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Device identifier</strong> — a persistent device ID derived from Android settings (e.g. ANDROID_ID) or a generated UUID, used to manage credits and sync data. We do not require account registration.</li>
      <li><strong>App settings</strong> — theme (dark/light), font scale, and font family stored locally on your device.</li>
      <li><strong>Design history</strong> — generated design metadata and image references stored locally (Room database) on your device.</li>
      <li><strong>Purchase information</strong> — transaction and entitlement data processed by Google Play and RevenueCat (we do not store full payment card details).</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics data</strong> — Firebase Analytics may collect app usage events, device type, OS version, and general interaction data.</li>
      <li><strong>Advertising data</strong> — when ads are shown, Google AdMob may collect advertising IDs and related data per Google’s policies.</li>
      <li><strong>Remote configuration</strong> — Firebase Remote Config fetches feature flags; no personal content is sent in config requests.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Generate AI interior design images from your room photos.</li>
      <li>Manage AI credits, purchases, and restore purchases.</li>
      <li>Store your design history on your device.</li>
      <li>Improve the App, fix bugs, and understand usage via analytics.</li>
      <li>Display ads when enabled (e.g. after closing the paywall without purchase).</li>
      <li>Deliver app updates and remote feature configuration.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Share Information</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Provider</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>AI processing API</td><td>Submit room images and prompts to generate designs</td><td>Our backend (hosted on Vercel)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Firebase Firestore</td><td>Store device credit balance</td><td>Google LLC</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Firebase Analytics</td><td>Usage analytics</td><td>Google LLC</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Firebase Remote Config</td><td>Feature flags and app configuration</td><td>Google LLC</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Google Play Billing</td><td>In-app purchases</td><td>Google LLC</td></tr>
        <tr><td>RevenueCat</td><td>Subscription and purchase management</td><td>RevenueCat, Inc.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Google AdMob</td><td>Rewarded interstitial advertising</td><td>Google LLC</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Unsplash (via CDN)</td><td>Style preview thumbnail images</td><td>Unsplash</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>We do not sell your personal information. We share data only as needed to operate the App or as required by law.</p>

    <h2>4. Data Storage &amp; Security</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Room photos are transmitted to our servers for AI processing; generated output URLs are returned to the App.</li>
      <li>Credit flags may be stored in encrypted local preferences (Android Keystore).</li>
      <li>Design history is stored locally on your device unless you delete it.</li>
      <li>We use industry-standard measures, but no method of transmission or storage is 100% secure.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Local design history remains until you delete it or uninstall the App.</li>
      <li>Server-side job data retention depends on our backend policies.</li>
      <li>Firestore device records persist while you use the App to maintain credit balance.</li>
      <li>Analytics data is retained per Google Firebase retention settings.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Your Choices &amp; Rights</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Photos</strong> — you choose when to upload; you can delete local history in the App.</li>
      <li><strong>Ads</strong> — premium users / when ads are disabled via configuration, paywall-dismiss ads are not shown.</li>
      <li><strong>Analytics</strong> — you may limit ad tracking in Android Settings → Google → Ads.</li>
      <li><strong>Uninstall</strong> — removes local app data; remote identifiers may persist per provider policies.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Depending on your region (e.g. EU/UK, California), you may have rights to access, correct, or delete personal data. Contact us below to exercise these rights.</p>

    <h2>7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>The App is not directed to children under 13 (or 16 in the EEA). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child provided data, contact us and we will delete it.</p>

    <h2>8. International Transfers</h2>
    <p>Your information may be processed in countries other than your own, including the United States, where our service providers operate. We rely on appropriate safeguards where required by law.</p>

    <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy. We will post the new version at this URL and update the “Last updated” date. Continued use after changes means you accept the updated policy.</p>

    <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>Questions about this Privacy Policy?<br />
    Email: <a href="mailto:support@jaystudio.ai">support@jaystudio.ai</a></p>

